===Adjective===
{{en-adj|-}}

# Of the same kind; [[alike]], [[similar]].
# Having the same [[composition]] throughout; of [[uniform]] make-up.
#* '''1946''', {{w|Bertrand Russell}}, ''History of Western Philosophy'', I.25:
#*: Their citizens were not of '''homogeneous''' origin, but were from all parts of Greece.
# {{lb|en|chemistry}} in the same [[state of matter]].
# {{lb|en|mathematics}} Of which the properties of a smaller set apply to the whole; [[scalable]].
#: ''The function <math>f(x,y)=x^2+y^2</math> is '''homogeneous''' of degree 2 because <math>f(\alpha x,\alpha y)=\alpha^2 f(x,y)</math>.''

